12:50.704 --> 12:52.604
Avery:
Hey. Sorry I'm late.

12:52.606 --> 12:54.773
Hey.
But I'm here now,
and I'm ready to do this.

12:54.775 --> 12:56.708
That's okay. I'm just
really glad you're here.

12:56.710 --> 12:58.810
You seemed kind of unsure
about taking the job last night.

12:58.812 --> 13:00.945
Well, I figure now's
as good a time as any,

13:00.947 --> 13:03.481
While cadence is still
small enough to shuttle around.

13:03.483 --> 13:05.416
Plus, how could I
turn down the chance

13:05.418 --> 13:07.385
To keep making great music
with you?
Oh, thank you.

13:08.488 --> 13:12.090
I can't believe this --
you, me, luke, riff.

13:12.092 --> 13:13.625
It's gonna be
the best night.

13:13.627 --> 13:15.393
Luke: Hi, avery.

13:15.395 --> 13:16.461
I just heard you were
joining the tour.

13:16.463 --> 13:17.428
Welcome aboard, son.
Thanks.

13:17.430 --> 13:18.563
Yeah, it was
kind of last minute,

13:18.565 --> 13:19.597
But I'm looking forward
to it.

13:19.599 --> 13:21.766
Well, uh,
that makes three of us.

13:21.768 --> 13:23.835
Um, you mind if I
steal layla here
for a quick second?

13:23.837 --> 13:25.036
Sure.
Yeah, I'll go plug in.
Okay.

13:26.106 --> 13:27.472
I just want you to know

13:27.474 --> 13:30.308
I'm so excited to be on tour
with you and with riff,

13:30.310 --> 13:31.976
And I was really hoping
to meet him

13:31.978 --> 13:33.344
Before everything
happens tonight,

13:33.346 --> 13:34.846
'cause he's a legend.
Uh, yeah.

13:34.848 --> 13:37.015
Yeah, might have to take
a rain check on that.

13:37.017 --> 13:39.684
Uh, something's come up.
Riff may not make it.

13:39.686 --> 13:41.953
But, uh, we're working to see
if we can fill the slot

13:41.955 --> 13:43.254
And still
put on the show.

13:43.256 --> 13:45.290
Wait. You might
cancel tonight altogether?

13:45.292 --> 13:46.891
Well, let's hope
it doesn't come to that.

13:52.132 --> 13:53.064
Okay.

13:55.869 --> 13:57.368
Listen, sweetie,

13:57.370 --> 13:59.537
She probably just
needs some space.

13:59.539 --> 14:01.172
That's all.
It's my fault.

14:01.174 --> 14:03.007
What are you
talking about?

14:03.009 --> 14:04.609
If I didn't say anything,

14:04.611 --> 14:06.978
You wouldn't have
known about the show,

14:06.980 --> 14:09.147
Sh-- she wouldn't have
run away.
No. No.

14:09.149 --> 14:11.282
Listen to m--
daphne, hey, hey, all right?

14:11.284 --> 14:14.219
Maddie made her choices, and
that is not your responsibility.

14:14.221 --> 14:16.888
You did exactly what you
should've done, all right?

14:19.326 --> 14:21.192
[ voice breaking ]
what if something bad happens?

14:21.194 --> 14:23.528
It won't.

14:23.530 --> 14:25.129
All right? I promise.

14:27.701 --> 14:28.800
[ knock on door ]

14:30.003 --> 14:31.502
Rayna,
what are you doing here?

14:31.504 --> 14:32.837
I'm looking for maddie.
Mind if I come in?

14:32.839 --> 14:34.038
By all means, please.

14:34.040 --> 14:36.474
Maddie?!

14:36.476 --> 14:38.576
She's not here.
Can I help you with something?

14:38.578 --> 14:40.211
You telling me
you don't know where she is?

14:40.213 --> 14:41.579
She hasn't
reached out to you?

14:41.581 --> 14:42.881
No,
I haven't talked to her.

14:42.883 --> 14:44.148
Why?
What's going on?
Maddie?!

14:44.150 --> 14:45.850
Because she ran away.

14:45.852 --> 14:47.919
Now, where'd she get
an idea like that?

14:47.921 --> 14:49.487
Maybe you should ask
your husband.

14:49.489 --> 14:50.655
Last time I saw her,

14:50.657 --> 14:52.257
He was practically
dragging her off a stage.

14:52.259 --> 14:53.892
I'm surprised
nobody even called the cops.

14:53.894 --> 14:56.194
I'm surprised nobody
called the cops on you.
[ scoffs ]

14:56.196 --> 14:58.196
She shouldn't have been on that
stage in the first place.

14:58.198 --> 14:59.264
Maddie!

14:59.266 --> 15:00.732
He was pretty aggressive
towards me, too.

15:00.734 --> 15:02.267
<i> Get off of her!</i>
<i> Dad!</i>

15:02.269 --> 15:04.002
<i> Why are you doing this?</i>

15:04.004 --> 15:05.603
You know, I don't have to
defend my husband to you.

15:05.605 --> 15:07.438
If you hear from her,
you call me.

15:07.440 --> 15:08.506
Get it?

15:12.679 --> 15:15.747
[ engine starts ]

15:15.749 --> 15:18.249
Hey.
You can come out.

15:19.452 --> 15:20.518
Is she gone?

15:20.520 --> 15:21.819
Yeah.

15:25.025 --> 15:26.124
So, what do you
want to do?

15:34.067 --> 15:35.533
You sure you're okay
going on the road as a nanny?

15:35.535 --> 15:38.403
I'm okay with it if you are.
Are you okay with it?

15:38.405 --> 15:40.238
Yeah, I'm fine. Why?

15:40.240 --> 15:42.106
Because you've fastened
and refastened that diaper

15:42.108 --> 15:43.775
About 20 times now.

15:43.777 --> 15:45.810
I'm just confused.

15:45.812 --> 15:47.278
Layla's going
on tour with luke,

15:47.280 --> 15:48.713
And now
avery's in her band?

15:48.715 --> 15:50.415
When did this happen?
I'm not sure.

15:50.417 --> 15:52.283
I know he was producing
her album, but --

15:52.285 --> 15:55.720
At least somebody's
moving forward in their career.

15:55.722 --> 15:56.988
But that means that

15:56.990 --> 15:58.923
He's taking my daughter
on the road with him,

15:58.925 --> 16:00.291
And I can't do anything
about it.

16:00.293 --> 16:02.093
Have you tried telling him
how you feel?

16:02.095 --> 16:04.662
What am I supposed to do?
He has all the power.

16:04.664 --> 16:07.298
He's got custody.
[ cadence cooing ]

16:07.300 --> 16:08.967
Guess I should
just be lucky

16:08.969 --> 16:10.168
That he's letting me
come visit.

16:10.170 --> 16:12.103
Which is definitely
progress.

16:12.105 --> 16:13.671
You're right.

16:13.673 --> 16:15.473
After everything
I put that man through,

16:15.475 --> 16:17.175
I guess I should
just be grateful

16:17.177 --> 16:20.311
That he and I
are in an okay place.

16:20.313 --> 16:23.147
What if riff's just sick
or hung over or something?

16:23.149 --> 16:25.817
I doubt luke would consider
canceling for a hangover.

16:25.819 --> 16:27.652
But he's looking for
a replacement, right?

16:27.654 --> 16:29.587
I'm sure
he's gonna find someone.
What if he doesn't?

16:29.589 --> 16:31.756
Tonight is supposed to be
a big step for me.

16:31.758 --> 16:33.458
You know,
I'm finally back on tour,

16:33.460 --> 16:34.792
I'm launching my album,

16:34.794 --> 16:36.928
And all that progress just stops
on the first night.

16:36.930 --> 16:37.996
It sucks.

16:39.466 --> 16:42.800
Maybe not.
What if we just film this?

16:42.802 --> 16:45.603
Sound check?
Yeah, why not?

16:45.605 --> 16:47.872
I mean, we already have
the band, the cameras,

16:47.874 --> 16:50.174
The incredibly talented
singer.

16:50.176 --> 16:51.342
This way,
if tonight is cancelled,

16:51.344 --> 16:52.510
At least we have something
to show for it.

16:52.512 --> 16:54.512
Okay.

16:54.514 --> 16:55.546
[ cellphone rings ]

16:55.548 --> 16:56.814
You find her?

16:56.816 --> 16:59.183
No, I didn't find her.
Damn it.

16:59.185 --> 17:01.552
Did you check every room?
You check every closet?

17:01.554 --> 17:03.454
I mean, you looked everywhere,
right?
I searched.

17:03.456 --> 17:04.822
As much as I could,
I searched.

17:04.824 --> 17:07.225
Cash told me
she wasn't there.
[ sighs ]

17:07.227 --> 17:09.627
[ sighs ] and then cash showed
me that video of last night.

17:09.629 --> 17:11.529
It was intense, deacon.
So, what are you saying?

17:11.531 --> 17:13.831
It's my fault now?
Is that what?
No.

17:13.833 --> 17:15.967
[ sighs ]
we know maddie's
got issues with your anger,

17:15.969 --> 17:17.568
And -- and maybe
she got freaked out.

17:17.570 --> 17:19.137
Baby, what was I
supposed to do,

17:19.139 --> 17:20.738
Leave her up there
singing half-dressed

17:20.740 --> 17:23.207
In front of a roomful of idiots
hooting and holler--

17:23.209 --> 17:24.575
Did you see the guy
grab her leg?

17:24.577 --> 17:28.312
Honey, I probably would've done
the exact same thing, okay?

17:28.314 --> 17:30.681
I just think that
we should be aware of

17:30.683 --> 17:32.216
What her frame of mind
might be.

17:32.218 --> 17:35.586
Okay. Fine.

17:36.689 --> 17:40.058
But none of that changes the
fact that she ain't home yet.

17:40.060 --> 17:41.993
They just don't support me
at all, you know?

17:41.995 --> 17:44.195
Neither of them.
I'm so sick of it.

17:44.197 --> 17:46.831
That's not exactly true,
maddie.

17:46.833 --> 17:49.500
I mean, your mom
did give you a record deal.
Whatever.

17:49.502 --> 17:51.602
That was only to keep me
from signing with sony.

17:51.604 --> 17:53.438
Sony offered you
a deal?

17:53.440 --> 17:55.173
Yeah.

17:55.175 --> 17:56.174
That's huge.

17:56.176 --> 17:58.242
I know,
but that was months ago.

17:58.244 --> 17:59.243
They could still
be interested.

17:59.245 --> 18:01.179
Look, I've got contacts
over there.

18:01.181 --> 18:02.380
If you want, I can call

18:02.382 --> 18:04.182
And see if the offer
still stands.

18:04.184 --> 18:06.350
Wait. Seriously?
You'd do that?

18:06.352 --> 18:08.186
Maddie, I would do anything
to help.

18:08.188 --> 18:10.254
Thank you.

18:10.256 --> 18:12.123
In a town
full of country singers,

18:12.125 --> 18:14.092
Not one of them can do me
a 45-minute favor.

18:14.094 --> 18:15.526
I'm not asking
for the moon.

18:15.528 --> 18:18.463
It's hard to lock down people
on such short notice.

18:18.465 --> 18:20.031
I still have calls out

18:20.033 --> 18:22.400
To dierks, blake,
and thomas rhett.

18:22.402 --> 18:24.135
Well, I don't think
we can count on riff,

18:24.137 --> 18:26.104
So let's hope
one of them steps up.

18:26.106 --> 18:28.873
At this rate,
it's our only shot.

18:28.875 --> 18:30.775
[ knock on door ]

18:30.777 --> 18:32.777
Heidi,
tell me you found riff.

18:32.779 --> 18:34.312
I just got a call from
a hospital in new orleans.

18:34.314 --> 18:35.546
He's been admitted.

18:35.548 --> 18:37.915
I won't know anything more
until I get down there.

18:37.917 --> 18:39.150
I was hoping
you could help.

18:39.152 --> 18:41.285
Uh, of course.
We'll go right now.

18:41.287 --> 18:42.553
Keep trying, kenneth.
Yeah.

18:42.555 --> 18:44.255
Yeah, come on.

18:44.257 --> 18:46.624
So, I ran into riley at crema
the other day.

18:46.626 --> 18:48.593
You two talk lately?

18:48.595 --> 18:49.961
No,
not since we broke up.

18:49.963 --> 18:51.329
Mm.
It's been a while.

18:51.331 --> 18:52.997
Maybe I should call, huh?

18:52.999 --> 18:56.167
You really should.
You two were good together.

18:56.169 --> 18:58.769
Hey,
I'll see you in there.
All right.

18:58.771 --> 19:01.239
[ sighs ]
it sucks, huh?

19:02.475 --> 19:04.008
Breakups, I mean.

19:04.010 --> 19:06.577
Yeah, that's --
that's the worst.

19:06.579 --> 19:09.747
All you can do is learn from it
and move on, right?

19:09.749 --> 19:10.815
Yeah, totally.

19:13.119 --> 19:15.186
You mind if I --
if I join ya?

19:15.188 --> 19:16.687
Not at all.

