21:09.535 --> 21:11.602
[ cellphone rings ]
what's going on, will?

21:11.604 --> 21:12.803
How can you tell
if a guy is gay?

21:12.805 --> 21:14.739
Uh, if this is a joke,

21:14.741 --> 21:16.474
I'm not sure I want to hear
the punch line.

21:16.476 --> 21:18.142
No, no, no. I'm serious,
and I need your help.

21:18.144 --> 21:21.279
I just met this guy,
and I can't tell.

21:21.281 --> 21:24.148
I mean, uh, he's one of
my backup singers,

21:24.150 --> 21:26.717
And, oh, he just broke up
with someone named riley,

21:26.719 --> 21:27.918
So gay, right?

21:27.920 --> 21:30.454
Well, given those
<i> very</i> limited details,

21:30.456 --> 21:32.256
It's possible,

21:32.258 --> 21:34.125
Though riley can be
a girl's name, too.

21:34.127 --> 21:35.760
Oh, and he did say
he's into cars and football

21:35.762 --> 21:36.961
And grilling and stuff.

21:36.963 --> 21:38.062
So, uh --
so he's straight.

21:38.064 --> 21:39.497
You like those things,
will.

21:39.499 --> 21:41.098
Well, then,
how am I supposed to know

21:41.100 --> 21:42.600
If he's
a potential suitor --

21:42.602 --> 21:44.101
Whatever you called them?

21:44.103 --> 21:45.836
Look, if you really
want to know if he's gay,

21:45.838 --> 21:47.638
Man up and ask him out.

21:49.275 --> 21:51.242
I never knew
a bunch of hot rocks

21:51.244 --> 21:52.510
Could be so relaxing.

21:52.512 --> 21:53.744
[ chuckles ]

21:53.746 --> 21:55.079
Yeah, trust me.

21:55.081 --> 21:57.515
This and some good scotch

21:57.517 --> 22:00.518
Are the only way to survive
these long tours.

22:00.520 --> 22:02.753
[ chuckles ]
just something you're gonna
want to keep in mind.

22:02.755 --> 22:05.323
I can't thank you enough
for bringing us out here.

22:05.325 --> 22:07.325
Oh, yes, you can,
and you have.

22:07.327 --> 22:09.093
Anyway, the way
your single's blowing up,

22:09.095 --> 22:10.695
Having you here
is good for all of us.

22:10.697 --> 22:13.698
Well, it means a lot to me --
and gunnar, too.

22:16.469 --> 22:19.370
Hey, I know I promised
not to pry,

22:19.372 --> 22:22.106
But I have to say,

22:22.108 --> 22:25.042
It's really hard to believe
there isn't something

22:25.044 --> 22:26.610
Still going on
between you guys.

22:26.612 --> 22:27.878
How do you mean?

22:27.880 --> 22:30.114
You know,
I've watched you play.

22:30.116 --> 22:33.117
You chemistry, your energy.

22:33.119 --> 22:34.585
There's a lot more going on
than just music.

22:36.622 --> 22:38.956
If I can be completely honest
with you...
Yeah?

22:38.958 --> 22:42.226
...There always<i> is</i>
something going on

22:42.228 --> 22:44.528
Just under the surface
with me and gunnar,

22:44.530 --> 22:48.232
But we decided
for the good of the band that...

22:48.234 --> 22:49.800
That's just where
it's got to stay.

22:50.903 --> 22:52.536
Very smart girl.

22:52.538 --> 22:55.740
Take it from someone with
a few more miles behind her,

22:55.742 --> 22:57.675
It is never a good idea

22:57.677 --> 22:59.710
To complicate these things
out on the road.

22:59.712 --> 23:01.479
[ chuckles ]

23:01.481 --> 23:02.513
[ chuckling ] just another
one of those things

23:02.515 --> 23:03.981
You might want
to keep in mind.

23:03.983 --> 23:06.484
Thank you.

23:06.486 --> 23:08.853
I-I feel like I'm really
gonna learn a lot from you.

23:08.855 --> 23:10.388
Oh.

23:10.390 --> 23:12.289
Mrs. Bell?

23:13.493 --> 23:14.425
I'm dr. Goff.

23:14.427 --> 23:15.993
I'm overseeing
your husband's care.

23:15.995 --> 23:17.595
Is he all right?
I want to see him.

23:17.597 --> 23:19.330
Can you tell us
what happened?

23:19.332 --> 23:20.998
Maybe you'd prefer
to speak privately, ma'am.

23:21.000 --> 23:22.767
No, no. It's okay.

23:22.769 --> 23:24.869
He's a friend,
and he needs to know, too.
Very well.

23:24.871 --> 23:26.771
There's no easy way
to say this.

23:26.773 --> 23:28.372
Your husband was
admitted to the icu

23:28.374 --> 23:29.840
After a woman brought him in
late last night.

23:29.842 --> 23:30.841
What woman?

23:30.843 --> 23:32.376
A local escort.

23:32.378 --> 23:35.446
According to her,
mr. Bell became unresponsive

23:35.448 --> 23:38.015
After several days
of consuming

23:38.017 --> 23:40.418
Dangerous amounts of alcohol,
pain pills,

23:40.420 --> 23:42.586
And sexual performance
enhancers.

23:42.588 --> 23:44.688
Y-y-you sure we're talking
about the same guy, doc?

23:44.690 --> 23:46.056
Quite sure, sadly.

23:46.058 --> 23:48.225
His toxicity report
confirms it,

23:48.227 --> 23:49.894
And it suggests
that it's the cause

23:49.896 --> 23:51.362
Of his brain hemorrhage.

23:51.364 --> 23:52.930
Oh, my god.
W-what does that mean?

23:52.932 --> 23:54.398
When can he come home
and do a show?

23:54.400 --> 23:57.635
Just to clarify,
the patient had a stroke.

23:57.637 --> 23:59.603
He's still unconscious.

23:59.605 --> 24:01.505
He certainly won't be onstage
anytime soon.

24:04.977 --> 24:06.577
[ door slams, purse thuds ]
[ grunts ]

24:06.579 --> 24:09.480
What is wrong?
Did your meeting not go well?

24:09.482 --> 24:11.315
Oh, what meeting?
What meeting?

24:11.317 --> 24:12.750
No, luke bailed. Bailed.

24:12.752 --> 24:14.752
And I had to watch
avery and layla

24:14.754 --> 24:16.654
Grind onstage
during sound check.

24:16.656 --> 24:19.290
[ sighs ]
is there something
going on between them?

24:19.292 --> 24:20.491
Not that I know of.

24:20.493 --> 24:21.826
Would you tell me
if there was?

24:21.828 --> 24:23.327
Well, of course.

24:23.329 --> 24:25.162
But you want to tell me
what's really bothering you?

24:25.164 --> 24:28.632
It's just, I've been trying to
get my life back together.

24:28.634 --> 24:31.502
My career, my daughter,
my team -- everything --

24:31.504 --> 24:34.638
And avery is the only
missing puzzle piece.

24:34.640 --> 24:38.075
And...I thought we had
this moment this morning.

24:38.077 --> 24:39.109
We've been getting along
so well.

24:39.111 --> 24:40.978
We had this spark,

24:40.980 --> 24:42.980
And then I see him onstage
with her.

24:42.982 --> 24:46.317
It's --
oh, god.
I'm so sorry, juliette.

24:46.319 --> 24:48.319
You know, maybe
it's just not meant to be.

24:48.321 --> 24:51.956
Yeah, maybe
I just don't deserve him.

24:51.958 --> 24:53.924
I'm just not ready
to let go yet.

24:53.926 --> 24:55.259
But it's gonna be okay,

24:55.261 --> 24:57.261
Because you're gonna be
on the road,

24:57.263 --> 24:59.163
Keeping an eye on him.

25:00.466 --> 25:01.398
Right?

25:02.301 --> 25:03.667
Sure.

25:06.005 --> 25:07.371
Yeah. Mm-hmm.

25:10.109 --> 25:12.543
Layla:
Wait. Wait. No peeking.

25:12.545 --> 25:15.145
Okay.
Okay, all right, now.

25:15.147 --> 25:16.647
Ta-da.

25:16.649 --> 25:19.283
Oh, wow. Look at this.

25:19.285 --> 25:22.453
[ laughs ]
you got pro tools,
mixer.

25:22.455 --> 25:24.221
Mm-hmm.
Aw, man,
this is a great setup.

25:24.223 --> 25:25.623
This your idea?
Yeah.

25:25.625 --> 25:27.558
Well, as soon as you said yes,
I had them put it in

25:27.560 --> 25:29.293
So we can keep recording
on the road.

25:29.295 --> 25:30.194
And...

25:33.633 --> 25:34.899
I had them put in a crib
for cadence

25:34.901 --> 25:36.033
So you won't
have to worry about

25:36.035 --> 25:37.434
Cramming into a bunk
or anything.

25:38.571 --> 25:40.004
Wait.

25:40.006 --> 25:42.473
You're giving me
your bedroom?
Yeah.

25:42.475 --> 25:44.975
I can't imagine it's gonna be
easy touring with an infant,

25:44.977 --> 25:46.744
So you should be
comfortable.

25:50.550 --> 25:51.348
What's wrong?

25:51.350 --> 25:53.484
Uh...

25:53.486 --> 25:55.052
I just need a second.

25:59.592 --> 26:01.825
So, apparently, this wasn't
just any record deal.

26:01.827 --> 26:03.861
Sony was offering you
the works --

26:03.863 --> 26:06.931
A huge advance, big marketing,
massive royalties.

26:06.933 --> 26:08.532
They basically
wanted to make you

26:08.534 --> 26:10.067
The next taylor
or miranda.

26:10.069 --> 26:12.870
Wow. Only my mom would kill
an opportunity that good.

26:12.872 --> 26:14.238
It's not dead.

26:15.441 --> 26:17.541
Sony's still interested
if you are.
Really?

26:17.543 --> 26:19.243
[ chuckles ]

26:19.245 --> 26:22.379
But I'm -- I'm still under
that contract with highway 65.

26:22.381 --> 26:24.114
I mean, even if my parents
would let me go,

26:24.116 --> 26:26.517
I would still need their consent
to sign with sony.

26:26.519 --> 26:29.620
It's like no matter where I go,
they're just in my way.

26:29.622 --> 26:30.621
Yeah, listen.

26:32.425 --> 26:33.724
[ sighs ]

26:33.726 --> 26:35.392
On that call,

26:35.394 --> 26:37.661
I found out something
that I think you should know.

26:40.099 --> 26:41.865
Okay.
Well, thanks, valerie.
[ deacon sighs ]

26:41.867 --> 26:43.267
I appreciate your time,
and, yeah,

26:43.269 --> 26:44.602
We'll let you know
if we hear anything.

26:44.604 --> 26:47.204
[ cellphone clicks ]
and what's
the lawyer say?

26:47.206 --> 26:48.372
Well, she says basically

26:48.374 --> 26:50.207
We just need to keep doing
what we're doing.

26:50.209 --> 26:52.142
[ scoffs ]
you know, calling people
and searching.

26:52.144 --> 26:54.445
Great.
That's real, real helpful.

26:54.447 --> 26:55.913
The only other option
is we get the police involved.

26:55.915 --> 26:57.815
Then,
why don't we do that?

26:57.817 --> 26:59.249
Because as soon as
the police are involved,

26:59.251 --> 27:00.317
We got to file a report,

27:00.319 --> 27:02.286
And then she's in the system
as a runaway.

27:02.288 --> 27:03.621
Well, she<i> is</i> a runaway,
rayna.

27:03.623 --> 27:05.289
But, hon, the minute
that she's in the system,

27:05.291 --> 27:07.057
Suddenly anybody
can get ahold of that.

27:07.059 --> 27:08.459
I mean,
that's public knowledge.

27:08.461 --> 27:10.060
That can be dragged
through the tabloids.

27:10.062 --> 27:11.462
I don't want that for her.
All right, great.

27:11.464 --> 27:12.763
We can't do this.
We can't do that.

27:12.765 --> 27:14.765
What can we do?
I don't know!

27:14.767 --> 27:16.634
I'm trying to figure it out
same as you are.

27:16.636 --> 27:18.002
[ sighs ]

27:18.004 --> 27:19.637
Good lord, deacon.

27:19.639 --> 27:21.438
Why'd you have to blow up on her
like that last night?

27:21.440 --> 27:23.741
You have no idea what it was
like in there, rayna!

27:23.743 --> 27:24.908
All right?!
What was I supposed to say?!

27:24.910 --> 27:26.276
"excuse me, young man.

27:26.278 --> 27:27.544
When you're done
groping my daughter's leg,

27:27.545 --> 27:28.811
Can I have a little word
with you over here?"

27:28.814 --> 27:31.515
What was I
supposed to do?!
I don't know.

27:31.517 --> 27:33.317
But I do know what it is
to be a 16-year-old girl

27:33.319 --> 27:35.352
And have a fight with
your father and leave
the house forever.

27:35.354 --> 27:37.888
And I don't want that
for maddie.

27:39.759 --> 27:41.325
I don't, either.

27:41.327 --> 27:44.561
¶¶

27:50.836 --> 27:52.302
I'm just scared to death,

27:52.304 --> 27:54.705
And I don't...
Know our next move.

27:56.175 --> 27:58.075
I thought of one place
we haven't looked yet.

28:02.848 --> 28:04.148
I don't get it.

28:04.150 --> 28:06.050
Going off the deep
end like that

28:06.052 --> 28:07.484
Seems so unlike him.

28:07.486 --> 28:08.852
Does it?

28:08.854 --> 28:11.288
[ scoffs ] come on.

28:11.290 --> 28:13.624
He was always like this
on the road --

28:13.626 --> 28:17.394
The parties, the groupies.

28:17.396 --> 28:19.863
You must remember.

28:19.865 --> 28:21.665
Yeah, I do. I just --

28:21.667 --> 28:24.068
I guess I thought those days
were behind him.

28:24.070 --> 28:25.202
Me too.

28:26.572 --> 28:29.573
You know, it eventually got so
bad I had to put my foot down.

28:29.575 --> 28:31.475
I made him retire.

28:31.477 --> 28:34.678
Figured it was the only way
to save him, save us,

28:34.680 --> 28:36.246
And it stuck for a while.

28:36.248 --> 28:39.416
At least, I thought it did.

28:39.418 --> 28:42.152
Truth is, after he played
the beverly last week,

28:42.154 --> 28:43.987
He never came home.

28:43.989 --> 28:45.756
Hell,
I am so sorry, heidi.

28:45.758 --> 28:47.925
I never would've
brought him back out

28:47.927 --> 28:50.461
Had I known the temptation
would be too --
it is not your fault.

28:52.064 --> 28:54.064
It's like an addiction
to him.

28:54.066 --> 28:56.166
I had no idea.

28:56.168 --> 28:57.267
I could tell.

28:57.269 --> 28:59.436
The way you looked at
our family,

28:59.438 --> 29:01.839
You saw perfection.

29:01.841 --> 29:03.040
But it wasn't.

29:03.042 --> 29:05.409
Nothing ever is.

29:05.411 --> 29:07.111
No, it sure ain't.

29:08.547 --> 29:09.947
[ sighs ]

29:09.949 --> 29:11.281
Thank you so much, luke.

29:11.283 --> 29:13.517
Yeah.
Yeah.

29:13.519 --> 29:15.252
I can handle things
from here.

29:15.254 --> 29:16.720
Are you sure?

29:16.722 --> 29:18.155
You've got a show to do.

29:22.728 --> 29:24.928
[ knock on door ]

29:24.930 --> 29:27.131
Hey.
Hey.

29:27.133 --> 29:28.398
I wasn't sure
where you went.

29:28.400 --> 29:29.867
Yeah, sorry.

29:29.869 --> 29:32.369
I just needed a minute
to clear my head,

29:32.371 --> 29:33.670
Process everything.

29:35.407 --> 29:38.742
Look, I know this tour stuff
happened really fast.

29:38.744 --> 29:41.478
I just -- I hope I didn't
rush you into anything.

29:41.480 --> 29:43.213
No.

29:43.215 --> 29:44.381
No, it's -- it's --
it's not that.

29:44.383 --> 29:45.315
It's just...

29:46.552 --> 29:49.219
In fact, this is exactly
what I need --

29:49.221 --> 29:50.888
The job, the bus.

29:50.890 --> 29:55.125
And you've been
so thoughtful and generous.

29:56.595 --> 29:59.730
I guess
I'm just not used to it.

29:59.732 --> 30:01.298
You know, being --

30:01.300 --> 30:04.168
Being put ahead of
someone else.

30:04.170 --> 30:05.302
It means a lot.

30:05.304 --> 30:06.570
So thank you.

30:06.572 --> 30:08.906
You deserve it.

30:08.908 --> 30:10.908
[ knock on door, door opens ]

30:10.910 --> 30:12.743
Hey.
You guys better get ready.

30:12.745 --> 30:14.011
Luke found a replacement.

30:14.013 --> 30:15.145
Looks like we've got a show
tonight after all.

30:15.147 --> 30:16.914
Yes!
[ chuckles ]

30:16.916 --> 30:18.081
Noel: Good news, guys,

30:18.083 --> 30:19.817
I got new numbers
on the single.

30:19.819 --> 30:21.485
We just hit 10,000.

30:21.487 --> 30:23.287
[ gasps ]
oh, my goodness!
Can you believe it?

30:23.289 --> 30:24.154
[ laughs ]
no.

30:24.156 --> 30:25.322
At this rate,
you're gonna be

30:25.324 --> 30:26.590
Hanging up gold records
in no time.

30:26.592 --> 30:28.692
And I'm getting tons
of phone calls for press.

30:28.694 --> 30:30.594
<i> Billboard, rolling stone,</i>

30:30.596 --> 30:32.129
And a bunch of others.
Whoa.

30:32.131 --> 30:33.831
Wow.
I'm really proud
of you two.

30:33.833 --> 30:35.933
You've earned this.

30:35.935 --> 30:38.001
Thank you.
Thank you, man.

30:38.003 --> 30:40.103
[ sighs ] I mean,
it's pretty incredible, right?

30:40.105 --> 30:41.872
It's something else.
I don't know what to do.

30:41.874 --> 30:45.943
So, um, h-how did it go with --
with autumn today?

30:45.945 --> 30:47.878
Tiny fish
nibbled on my feet.

30:47.880 --> 30:49.680
It was awesome.

30:49.682 --> 30:50.514
Is that normal?

30:50.516 --> 30:52.216
I don't know.
I don't care.

30:52.218 --> 30:54.017
She's been a role model for me
for so long,

30:54.019 --> 30:56.653
And now she's becoming
my friend.

30:56.655 --> 30:58.522
It's really cool.
Yeah.

30:58.524 --> 31:00.324
Yeah, I'm --
I'm really happy for you.

31:00.326 --> 31:02.292
You guys should hang out
one-on-one sometime.

31:02.294 --> 31:03.393
I think you'd like her.

31:03.395 --> 31:05.963
[ chuckles ]

31:05.965 --> 31:08.465
Hey, uh,
I just wanted to say thanks

31:08.467 --> 31:10.234
For letting me sing
on your record.

31:10.236 --> 31:12.836
I got a good feeling
about it.
Yeah. Yeah, me too.

31:12.838 --> 31:14.938
All right.
I'll see you around.

31:16.375 --> 31:17.407
Hey -- hey, bryan.

31:18.577 --> 31:20.677
Uh, do you feel like

31:20.679 --> 31:22.145
Grabbing a beer
or something?

31:23.682 --> 31:24.848
Sure.

31:24.850 --> 31:26.049
Yeah, I'd love to.

31:26.051 --> 31:28.385
Well, all right.

31:28.387 --> 31:29.386
[ knock on door ]

31:31.156 --> 31:33.090
Hey.
Hi.

31:33.092 --> 31:34.725
Sorry to bother you.

31:34.727 --> 31:36.927
Um, I'm looking for maddie.

31:36.929 --> 31:38.562
Is she here,
by any chance?

31:38.564 --> 31:40.731
No, she's not.
Is everything okay?

31:40.733 --> 31:45.402
[ sighs ]
no, it really isn't.

31:45.404 --> 31:47.237
[ crying ]

31:48.707 --> 31:50.274
Talked to cash?

31:50.276 --> 31:52.042
Sure have.

31:52.044 --> 31:54.745
She say anything
about maddie?

31:54.747 --> 31:56.446
I'm not looking
for me and my daughter

31:56.448 --> 31:57.915
To get caught up
in whatever this is

31:57.917 --> 31:59.283
Between you and yours.

31:59.285 --> 32:01.218
Yeah, well, your daughter
put herself right in the middle.

32:01.220 --> 32:02.185
I'm sorry.
So I'm just asking,

32:02.187 --> 32:03.353
As a friend here
and a father,

32:03.355 --> 32:04.454
What have you heard,
frankie?

32:04.456 --> 32:06.556
Just that cash
took maddie out

32:06.558 --> 32:08.792
To play a little music
last night

32:08.794 --> 32:10.761
And you lost
your damn mind.

32:10.763 --> 32:12.629
She took a minor into a bar
without permission.

32:12.631 --> 32:14.097
That's what she did.

32:14.099 --> 32:16.266
I seem to recall you
bringing her in here, too,

32:16.268 --> 32:18.268
And this is a bar.
It's not the same thing.

32:18.270 --> 32:19.369
You know that, frankie.

32:19.371 --> 32:20.971
Come on now.
Still no reason for you

32:20.973 --> 32:23.040
To blow up on cash
like you did.
I swear to god,

32:23.042 --> 32:25.409
I don't know how this
keeps getting put back
on me, all right?

32:25.411 --> 32:27.044
I was there
to protect my daughter.

32:27.046 --> 32:28.912
That is all.
I did the right thing.

32:28.914 --> 32:30.580
If you did
the right thing,

32:30.582 --> 32:32.683
Why you suppose
maddie ran away?

32:36.956 --> 32:39.556
I had no idea you were
going through all that with her.

32:39.558 --> 32:41.892
Yeah, we've had
a rough go of it,

32:41.894 --> 32:45.295
Really ever since she went
onstage with you in atlanta.

32:45.297 --> 32:46.930
I'm sorry.

32:46.932 --> 32:48.565
Hey,
I'm not blaming you.

32:48.567 --> 32:51.001
It's what maddie wants,
you know?

32:51.003 --> 32:53.103
I keep trying to do things

32:53.105 --> 32:56.807
To slow her down
a little bit, but...

32:56.809 --> 32:58.909
There's just no containing her
at this point.

32:58.911 --> 33:01.078
I don't think
there was anything

33:01.080 --> 33:03.146
That could contain us
at 16.

33:03.148 --> 33:04.982
But I get it.

33:04.984 --> 33:08.151
As a mom going through
what I have,

33:08.153 --> 33:11.355
I understand
that desire to hold on.

33:11.357 --> 33:14.191
It seems like the more
I try to hold on,

33:14.193 --> 33:16.693
The more she just
pushes me away.

33:16.695 --> 33:18.161
What are you gonna do?

33:18.163 --> 33:21.965
Even when they push away,
you just --

33:21.967 --> 33:25.202
How do you let go of somebody
that you love?

33:25.204 --> 33:27.270
You don't.

33:33.212 --> 33:35.512
Man: All right, country fans,
put your hands together

33:35.514 --> 33:37.014
For tonight's special guest,
thomas rhett.

33:37.016 --> 33:39.883
[ cheers and applause ]

33:39.885 --> 33:42.586
[ "die a happy man" plays ]

33:45.791 --> 33:48.492
¶ baby, last night ¶

33:48.494 --> 33:50.961
¶ was hands down ¶

33:50.963 --> 33:54.164
¶ one of the best nights ¶

33:54.166 --> 33:57.334
¶ that I've had, no doubt ¶

33:57.336 --> 34:00.137
¶ between the bottle of wine
and the look in your eyes ¶

34:00.139 --> 34:02.706
¶ and the marvin gaye ¶

34:02.708 --> 34:06.009
¶ then we danced in the dark
under September stars ¶

34:06.011 --> 34:08.412
¶ in the pourin' rain ¶

34:08.414 --> 34:11.815
¶ and I know that I can't ¶

34:11.817 --> 34:14.084
¶ ever tell you enough ¶

34:14.086 --> 34:17.087
¶ that all I need in this life ¶

34:17.089 --> 34:20.323
¶ is your crazy love ¶

34:20.325 --> 34:25.829
¶ if I never get to see
the northern lights ¶

34:25.831 --> 34:32.102
¶ or if I never get to see
the eiffel tower at night ¶

34:32.104 --> 34:37.941
¶ oh, if all I got
is your hand in my hand ¶

34:37.943 --> 34:42.679
¶ baby, I could die
a happy man ¶

34:42.681 --> 34:44.948
Luke: Whew!
Man, I owe him big time.

34:44.950 --> 34:48.685
Yeah.
Thomas is a great fix.

34:48.687 --> 34:50.687
But with old riff out,

34:50.689 --> 34:53.890
We need to find a more permanent
solution starting tomorrow.

34:53.892 --> 34:57.861
¶<i> baby, that red dress</i> ¶
or we could just pull the plug
and walk away right now.

34:57.863 --> 35:00.730
¶<i> brings me to my knees</i> ¶
I'm starting to feel like
this tour's done enough damage.

35:00.732 --> 35:03.100
¶<i> oh, but that black dress</i> ¶
what? You saying you just
want to cancel the tour?

35:03.102 --> 35:06.369
¶<i> makes it hard to breathe</i> ¶
no, because now
we're talking buy-backs...

35:06.371 --> 35:08.905
¶<i> you're a saint,</i>
<i> you're a goddess</i> ¶
...Lawsuits,
massive backlash.

35:08.907 --> 35:10.307
¶<i> the cutest, the hottest,</i>
<i> a masterpiece</i> ¶
luke, you turned
your reputation around, man.

35:10.309 --> 35:12.476
Now you just want
to throw it away?

35:12.478 --> 35:14.611
¶<i> it's too good to be true,</i>
<i> nothing better than you</i> ¶
I don't know what I want.

35:14.613 --> 35:15.946
[ knock on door ]

35:15.948 --> 35:17.981
¶<i> in my wildest dreams</i> ¶

35:17.983 --> 35:19.783
I'll give you two
a minute.

35:19.785 --> 35:20.984
¶<i> and you know that I can't</i> ¶
yeah.

35:20.986 --> 35:22.586
¶<i> ever tell you enough</i> ¶

35:22.588 --> 35:25.155
Hey.
Hey, yourself.

35:25.157 --> 35:26.723
¶<i> that all I need in this life</i>
<i> is your crazy love</i> ¶
what?
I leave for a couple months,

35:26.725 --> 35:29.626
